description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Staff Nurse – Surgery (Registered &amp; Newly Qualified)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Find the job you’re suited to……..&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a fast moving acute surgical unit aiming to provide outstanding care to patients having undergone life changing cardiac and thoracic surgery; these operations include heart and lung transplants, pulmonary thrombo-endartectomies, ventricular assist devices and various thoracic procedures. Our progressive care unit is an intermediate level of care facility that allows the early step down of patients from Critical Care to a ward area. We believe in giving you full support to ensure that you are equipped with the necessary skills so that you can feel confident caring for our patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Build your experience by joining our outstanding team and grow your competence in acute surgical management, identifying and managing deteriorating patients and responding to emergencies as well as complex discharge planning and physical rehabilitation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Join our friendly, dedicated and passionate team and develop your career with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Successful candidates will be highly motivated, energetic and will have excellent communication skills, be committed to delivering high quality through delivering improvement initiatives, and strive to ensure that care is continuously patient focused.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In addition to this we have a £1,000 welcome waiting for you *&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What our nurses say…..&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“We are a dynamic, supportive and friendly team who care for patients undergoing cardiac investigations as well as cardiac and thoracic surgery”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“Your career goals are important to us and we believe in supporting our staff to develop their experience, knowledge and skills”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“We have a wonderful team of experienced nurses with a good team spirit”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What our patients say…..&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“Just to say my stay for 8 days was enjoyable; staff could not have done any more for me even if they had tried. Everyone was very pleasant at all times and made my stay pleasant”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“What to say when ‘Thank You’ isn&#39;t enough. All staff are wonderful from the cleaners, people in the kitchen, nurses of all grades, doctors and anyone in between. Keep doing with what you are doing and you can&#39;t go wrong. Thank you so very much”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;“The staff were highly professional in every respect. I could not fault the treatment I received. I take my hat off to all the staff this truly excellent hospital”&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;Regular shortlisting takes place and you will be contacted for a Skype interview if you are shortlisted for interview.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;*£1,000 welcome payment applicable to those who commence on substantive contracts with a commitment to remain with the Trust for a minimum of 12 months (excludes Bank contracts).&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
